Minister of Energy Jeff Radebe was due to answer questions in the National Assembly on Wednesday afternoon. CAPE TOWN – Energy Minister Jeff Radebe has been rushed to the hospital due to ill-health, says Speaker Baleka Mbete. Radebe was due to answer parliamentary questions in the National Assembly on Wednesday afternoon, according to Speaker Baleka Mbete. “Honourable chief whips have been informed about the apology of the honourable Minister Jeff Radebe who was scheduled to answer questions today at 3 pm. He has had to be rushed to hospital on an emergency due to ill-health,” Mbete said. 